arch:property.oc:show_val: wood dock pilings, large unworked l-h whelk and horse conch shells, shaft-straightener lithic

Along the northeastern shore of the site fighting conch hammers are mixed in with Glades sherds and historic metal engine fragments. Mission period/Early Spanish sherds were observed on the southeastern shore.
